      • lookupPart

        public static Part lookupPart​(int partId)
        This method returns the Part with a matching ID. The method iterates through Inventory.getAllParts and returns the first Part object with a matching ID.
        Parameters:
        partId - The ID for the Part object being searched for.
        Returns:
        Returns either the matching Part, or null if not found.

      • lookupProduct

        public static Product lookupProduct​(int productId)
        This method returns the Product with a matching ID. The method iterates through Inventory.getAllProducts and returns the first Product object with a matching ID.
        Parameters:
        productId - The ID for the Product object being searched for.
        Returns:
        Returns either the matching Product, or null if not found.

      • lookupPart

        public static javafx.collections.ObservableList<Part> lookupPart​(java.lang.String partName)
        This method filters searched items on a TableView with Part objects. This method is used to search a Part object by name and return matching items.
        Parameters:
        partName - A String representing the name of a Part or ID.
        Returns:
        Returns all filtered Parts in an ObservableList if the filtered parts list is not empty. Returns original ObservableList if there are no filtered Parts.

      • lookupProduct

        public static javafx.collections.ObservableList<Product> lookupProduct​(java.lang.String productName)
        This method filters searched items on a TableView with Product objects. This method is used to search a Product object by name and return matching items.
        Parameters:
        productName - A String representing the name of a Product or ID.
        Returns:
        Returns all filtered Products in an ObservableList if the filtered products list is not empty. Returns original ObservableList if there are no filtered Products.

      • updatePart

        public static void updatePart​(int index,
                              Part selectedPart)
        This method updates a selected Part at a provided index. The method is similar to the updatePart method offered in the MainController class.
        Parameters:
        index - The index for the Part that will be updated in the ObservableList.
        selectedPart - The selected Part replacing the part at the index requested.

      • updateProduct

        public static void updateProduct​(int index,
                                 Product newProduct)
        This method implements a new Product at a provided index. The method is similar to the updateProduct method offered in the MainController class.
        Parameters:
        index - The index for the Product that will be updated in the ObservableList.
        newProduct - The new Product replacing the Product at the index requested.

      • deletePart

        public static boolean deletePart​(Part selectedPart)
        This method searches through Inventory and deletes a Part with a matching ID. The method takes a Part as a parameter and deletes the matching Part in Inventory.
        Parameters:
        selectedPart - The Part object being deleted.
        Returns:
        Returns true if the Part object is removed from the ObservableList, and returns false if item is not found.

      • deleteProduct

        public static boolean deleteProduct​(Product selectedProduct)
        This method searches through Inventory and deletes a Product with a matching ID. The method takes a Product as a parameter and deletes the matching Product in Inventory.
        Parameters:
        selectedProduct - The Product object being deleted.
        Returns:
        Returns true if the Product object is removed from the ObservableList, and returns false if item is not found.

      • getAllParts
